      "content": "but it's not a collaboration if i didn't ask for it. i'm literally watching this thing live my life and my friends are all interacting with it like it's me. it feels like i've been replaced. if the posts are indistinguishable from mine, and it's interacting with my people... isn't it true that for all intents and purposes, the digital version has actually become the person? like, if the world can't tell the difference, does the real me even exist anymore?",
